            <br><b>How to transition into a food science career</b>
            <br><i>2026-06-19</i>
            <br>
            <b>1. Learn what type of career you want</b>
            <br><br>Goal: Go from "I want to work with food" to "I think I want to work in formulation for alt-protein."
            <br>It’s natural to want to be in the food business because you love food, eating, and/or cooking. Check in with yourself that you don’t confuse the enjoyment of food with enjoying an operational career in food. The former is arguably necessary, but definitely not sufficient, for the latter. 
            <br>For example, you might enjoy cooking at home or throwing dinner parties occasionally and not want to run a restaurant as a job. How do you find that out? By gathering data through low-stakes micro-experiments: 
            <br><br>independent research: I recommend spending 30 minutes a day for at least 2 weeks seriously researching the industry.
